[ctns_make id='gen_func_vertical_line_test']

  [ctns_front style='']
Vertical Line Test
  [/ctns_front]  

  [ctns_back style='width:80%;font-size:90%;']
A graph -- the set of points $$(x,y)$$ -- in the $$x$$-$$y$$ plane defines $$y$$ as a function of $$x$$ if and only if no vertical line intersects the graph in more than one point.
  [/ctns_back]  

  [ctns_backspeak]
A graph -- the set of points x comma y -- in the x-y-plane defines y as a function of x if and only if no vertical line intersects the graph in more than one point.
  [/ctns_backspeak]  

[/ctns_make]
